			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You can download a Photoshop indexed palette file of the NTSC palette used by Nestopia from here, it's pretty accurate: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://thefox.aspekt.fi/nestopia-yuv-palette.pal">http://thefox.aspekt.fi/nestopia-yuv-palette.pal</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />Out of the ~50ish colors in that palette, you have to make 4 sets of 3 colors that are used by the sprites in every given frame that NES renders. Sprites are internally composed of 8x8 or 8x16 blocks, each of which can use one of those 4 sets of colors. You can also overlay several 8x8/8x16 blocks to get more than 3 colors in a 8x8/8x16 area, with the cost of sprite flickering becoming more of an issue.
<br />
<br />I'll let somebody else explain this in more depth. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>

