				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">It has one thing that is not configurable and that is really difficult to get used to if you previously get used to something else: left mouse button places a pixel (or draws a line, etc), right mouse button is color picker. Otherwise it is has pretty standart interface, and once you get used to this mouse layout, it turns out to be very comfortable.
<br />
<br />Another thing that Gale have and many graphics editors aren't is palette management - you can move colors around, arranging them in a certain order, which is very useful for conversion purposes.
<br />
<br />So this editor is certainly deserves some attention. Even if you will do most of work in Photoshop, it could help with specific tasks.</div>

