				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Hardware sprites are either all 8x8 or 8x16 (tall). There are 64 of them on the screen at once, and only 8 could be displayed in a single scanline. You can construct larger sprites from these hardware sprites, that's called metasprites.
<br />
<br />You can't overcome the scanline limit, though, so if there are situations in your game when more than 64 pixels of sprites could be placed on one scanline, you need to implement the sprite flicker, to make sprites at least somehow visible in these situations. That affects to the game design a lot, as you don't want to have too much flicker and should avoid it by using taller objects and smart placement them on the screen.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />My stuff at <a href="http://www.youtube.com/user/shiru8bit" class="postlink">YouTube</a>, <a href="http://soundcloud.com/shiru" class="postlink">SoundCloud</a></div>
					<br clear="all" /><br />

